commit.message: -add cmake project version properties

According to http://libdmtx.wikidot.com/libdmtx-on-windows-using-visual-studio the preprocessor definition _VISUALC_ has to be defined in order to compile with Visual Studio.
This is done because older VS versions don't provide snprintf.
I didn't check with older versions, but this is true for VS2010 but not for VS2015 and above. I couldn't check VS2012/13 though.
Since MS provides [predefined macros](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/cpp/preprocessor/predefined-macros) they can be used to distinguish between the cases.

To really stay backward compatible with some cases i don't know of, maybe VS versions < 6.0, the check could be altered to
#if defined(_VI) || defined(_MSC_VER) && (_MSC_VER < 1700)

Merge pull request #17 from jbweston/bugfix/decodeSchemeBase356

handle errors when decoding Base256 scheme

commit.message:
properly handle error when decoding Base256 scheme

Previously the library would cause the process to exit with code 40,
now we return a null pointer and plumb the error condition through
all call sites until we hit the API.

This changes the signature of 'DecodeDataStream', as it now
needs to signal an error condition in its return value.
